docs.text: synopsis : al simmons , top-notch assasin with a guilty conscience , dies in a fiery explosion and goes to hell .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: making a pact with malebolgia , a chief demon there , simmons returns to earth 5 years later reborn as spawn , a general in hell's army donning a necroplasmic costume replete with knives , chains , and a morphing cape .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sullen , wise cogliostro and flatulating , wisecracking violator vy for spawn's attention .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: comments : when todd mcfarlane left marvel comics ( where he had made a name for himself as a first-rate comic book penciller on the " spider-man " titles ) to join the newly-formed , creator-owned image comics , a new comic book legend was born : spawn .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: mcfarlane's " spawn " immediately became a commercial and critical success and a defining comic book series of the 1990s .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: mcfarlane created a hero who was not only original but visually intricate , allowing mcfarlane to utilize his knack for artistic detail to the max .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the early " spawn " issues brilliantly capture mcfarlane's genius at illustration and show his early attempts at writing .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: with the popularity of " spawn " and the success of the current warner bros . 's batman film franchise , a movie version of some sort seemed inevitable for spawn .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in the summer of 1997 , hence , new line cinema released spawn , a live-action film based on the groundbreaking series .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this topheavy exercise in violence and special effects unfortunately topples quickly and leaves fans of the comic book , like me , numbed by how much spawn misses the mark .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: what happened ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: why is spawn so bad ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: todd mcfarlane himself executive produced this disappointing misfire and even appears in a cameo .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i don't think , however , that his presence necessarily hurt ( or helped ) the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i place the blame , in part , on the recent hollywood trend , fueled by public demand apparently , for special effects blow-out movies utilizing the latest computer technology .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: these films focus upon the effects at the expense of everything else : character , plot , dialogue , etc . spawn , reflecting this trend , shows the audience one gratuitous scene after another populated with morphing characters and filled with unnecessary pyrotechnics .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: hardly a minute goes by in this film without fires , explosions , knives and chains appearing out of nowhere , glowing eyes , or constantly transforming demons .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a lot of it is visually interesting and technically solid , don't get me wrong , but , because the script and cast aren't engaging , spawn ultimately comes across like overwrought wallpaper ( the surface may capture the eye , but nothing exists underneath ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: spawn's translation of the comic book suffers the most at the storyline level .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: mcfarlane's spawn was a tortured hero .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a mercenary by trade , al simmons was nonetheless a warm man in love with the beautiful wanda .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: having died and journeyed to hell , he made a pact to return to earth to be with wanda .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: simmons , however , discovers that his memories are fragmented , his body a creepy mess , and his wife married .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: despite his sometimes violent nature , readers couldn't help but feel sympathetic toward his plight as the spawn of the underworld .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: spawn attempts to show all of this but does not spend nearly the time it should to do so .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when the characters are developed , they seem absurd rather than touching .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the cartoonish dialogue and implausible subplot ( a general possesses the antidote to a supervirus called heat-16 which he wishes to unleash to enslave the world ) do not help matters .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: spawn , in an apparent attempt to duplicate the success of batman , also unwisely spends too much time on a villain , the violator ( batman favored the joker over batman ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: john leguizamo , like jack nicholson in batman , receives top billing in the cast as the violator ; michael jai white ( al simmons / spawn ) is second .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i ordinarily find leguizamo an intensely annoying presence in films which seems to make him a perfect candidate for the violator .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film , however , spends so much time on the violator's offensive antics that they grate on the nerves .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: apparently meant to be the comic relief in the film ( as nicholson was in batman ) , especially when contrasted with the sullen spawn , the violator's lines are oftentimes grotesque and unfunny , leaving the audience wishing he would leave .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: leguizamo does a satisfactory job in the role , but he is seen far too often in the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: michael jai white , a relative newcomer to theatrical releases , seems to be an appealing actor , and he handles his role adequately , but we see little of him without various masks on .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: more time needed to be spent on white's character before he became spawn for the movie to pull at the heartstrings .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a special note should be made about martin sheen as the over-the-top , obnoxious , evil general wynn .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: easily the hammiest performance in the movie , it's hard to imagine how sheen mucked up his role so much ; after all , he played a vietnam assasin brilliantly in the great apocalypse now .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sheen's excessive demeanor do not help the audience accept him as a mastermind villain and comes as a surprise considering his extensive career in film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: many other elements conspire with the disappointing script and abundant special effects to drag spawn down .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: mtv-style , jerky , in-your-face editing is one of them .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: flames , for example , roll across the screen sometimes to announce a shift in setting .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: cogliostro , unlikely wannabe guide for spawn , serves as a poor narrator for the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he goofily tells the audience , at one point , that " how much of [spawn's] humanity is left remains to be seen , " as if the audience really cares as one violent sequence leads to another .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the music , finally , assaults the audience as much as the manic violence and offensive dialogue .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: loud and obnoxious hard rock fused with drum loops dominate some scenes .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: to be fair , however , marilyn manson's " long hard road out of hell " effectively compliments spawn's return to earth , while filter and the crystal method's " ( can't you ) trip like i do " proves a surprisingly fitting theme song .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for as good a comic book as it is , " spawn " did not spawn a good movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: spawn , instead , suffers from too much pomp and circumstance , and too little plot and character development .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it receives two stars for its technically well-done special effects .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: many other films , though , have equal , if not superior , special effects and are much better .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: rated pg-13 , spawn seems more violent than many r-rated movies and probably wouldn't be appropriate for the very young .
docs.label: negative
